#Touch command usage
1. Create a file using touch comamnd
tocuh file_name

2. Create multiple file
touch file1 file2 file4 ...

3. Change access time of a file to current time
touch -a filename

4. Chance access time of a file to specific time
touch -a -t[CC]YYMMDDhhmm.[ss] filename 
example setting a file access time to 01 dec 2022
touch -t -a 202212010710.10 filename
Earlier - -rw-r--r-- 1 ravi.sharma34 1049089 0 Apr 14 06:33 file
Now - -rw-r--r-- 1 ravi.sharma34 1049089 0 Dec  1  2022 file

5. Change modification time of a file to current time
touch -m file

6. Change modification time to a specific date
touch -t -m [CC]YYMMDDhhmm.ss filename
example setting a file access time to 01 dec 2025
touch -t 202512010710.10 file1
Earlier - -rw-r--r-- 1 ravi.sharma34 1049089 0 Apr 14 06:37 file1
now - -rw-r--r-- 1 ravi.sharma34 1049089 0 Dec  1  2025 file1

To chnage only access time use flag -t -a and for modification use flag -t -m and for changing both time use simple -t option.
